            <div class="article-faq">
                <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

                <details class="article-faq-item">
                    <summary>How accurate is OCR?</summary>
                    <p>Modern AI-powered OCR achieves 97–99% character-level accuracy on clean, high-resolution scans of printed text. For handwritten text, accuracy is typically 70–85%. Poor quality scans, low DPI, or unusual fonts reduce accuracy significantly.</p>
                </details>

                <details class="article-faq-item">
                    <summary>Does OCR work on handwritten documents?</summary>
                    <p>Modern OCR can handle clear, neat handwriting reasonably well. Cursive handwriting, poor penmanship, or faded ink significantly reduces accuracy. For best results with handwritten documents, ensure high contrast and use a tool that specifically supports handwriting recognition (ICR).</p>
                </details>

                <details class="article-faq-item">
                    <summary>Will OCR change the appearance of my PDF?</summary>
                    <p>No. OCR adds an invisible text layer behind the original image — the visual appearance of your PDF is completely unchanged. The document looks identical to before, but now has searchable, selectable, and copyable text.</p>
                </details>

                <details class="article-faq-item">
                    <summary>Can OCR handle multi-language documents?</summary>
                    <p>Yes, most modern OCR engines including the one powering PdfToolStack support mixed-language documents. Select all languages present in the document for best results. Performance on right-to-left languages (Arabic, Hebrew) and complex scripts (Chinese, Japanese, Korean) is excellent with modern AI OCR engines.</p>
                </details>

                <details class="article-faq-item">
                    <summary>Is OCR free?</summary>
                    <p>PdfToolStack offers OCR as a Pro feature, included with the $19/month subscription. Free trials are available. The OCR engine processes documents rapidly — a 10-page scanned document typically completes in under 30 seconds.</p>
                </details>

                <details class="article-faq-item">
                    <summary>What file formats does OCR work with?</summary>
                    <p>PdfToolStack's OCR tool processes PDF files. If you have an image file (JPG, PNG, TIFF) that you need to make searchable, first convert it to PDF using the <a href="/jpg-to-pdf">JPG to PDF tool</a>, then run OCR on the resulting PDF.</p>
                </details>
            </div>

